  "hasWeakener": [],
  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/nagaraja-cou1-decision-2025",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/nagaraja-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 V&V 40 credibility factors assessed. Twelve of thirteen factors achieve required credibility level. One factor (Test conditions) is below required level (achieved 1, required 2) due to single loading condition; this gap is accepted given ASTM F1717 regulatory precedent and the absence of dynamic loading requirements in the current submission scope. All three QoIs satisfy pre-established acceptance bounds (E/uval < 1.96, percent difference < 10%). The FEA modeling framework is assessed as credible for the stated COU. Material property dataset DS01 (dataVintage 2025-08-22) predates the September 2025 model mesh revision; the team determined by engineering judgment that the revision was not material to the dataset's relevance, and this determination is documented in the simulation plan revision memo dated 2025-09-18. No formal re-validation study was commissioned.",
